Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1076
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 34-30-37.
Synopsis: Liability connected with off-road vehicle use. Provides that
an owner, a spectator, and a promoter are immune from civil liability
arising from a claim brought by a participant or the participant's
personal representative concerning the damage to or the loss of the
participant's property or the participant's injury or death that results
from the inherent risks of off-road vehicle use.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Goss-Reaves, Commons
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Judiciary.
